GRACE: Here she comes!

1:10:42.720 --> 1:10:45.240
Here she comes, here she comes,
here she comes.

1:10:50.640 --> 1:10:52.080
It's a boy.

1:10:53.360 --> 1:10:55.000
It's a boy.

1:10:56.760 --> 1:10:58.760
Oh. Oh.

1:10:58.760 --> 1:11:01.600
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

1:11:01.600 --> 1:11:02.880
Oh, my God.

1:11:02.880 --> 1:11:06.080
Oh, my God.
You're crowning again.

1:11:06.080 --> 1:11:08.000
Okay.

1:11:08.000 --> 1:11:09.040
‐ Oh, God.

1:11:09.040 --> 1:11:10.240
Oh, God.

1:11:10.240 --> 1:11:12.520
I'm having the twins!

1:11:15.080 --> 1:11:17.440
‐ You need to go to the ER
right now.

1:11:17.440 --> 1:11:22.160
She's experiencing
a full placental abruption.

1:11:22.160 --> 1:11:23.160
You need to go.

1:11:24.560 --> 1:11:25.680
Now!

1:11:42.800 --> 1:11:45.320
‐ You're doing great, baby.
‐ Doing great, Lucy.

1:11:45.320 --> 1:11:48.440
Just push now.
Push.

1:11:48.440 --> 1:11:49.840
Push, Lucy, push.
ADRIAN: You're doing great.

1:11:49.840 --> 1:11:51.040
It's amazing.
You're doing just amazing.

1:11:51.040 --> 1:11:53.560
JOHN:
It's coming. It's coming.

1:11:53.560 --> 1:11:55.760
The baby's head is crowning
right now.

1:11:55.760 --> 1:11:58.640
Push.
‐

1:11:58.640 --> 1:12:02.080
JOHN: And here he is.
Our second baby boy.

1:12:18.800 --> 1:12:21.760
ADRIAN: This is hard, and it's
difficult to understand,

1:12:21.760 --> 1:12:25.560
but we will work
through this together.

1:12:25.560 --> 1:12:29.680
But these are ours, and it is a
critical time to create a bond.

1:12:32.040 --> 1:12:36.400
You know, we have
been through...a lot.

1:12:36.400 --> 1:12:38.040
And...

1:12:38.040 --> 1:12:39.720
this is not, um...

1:12:41.080 --> 1:12:44.280
You've been through a lot,
Luce...

1:12:44.280 --> 1:12:45.840
these last couple days, and...

1:12:50.520 --> 1:12:51.800
It's overwhelming.

1:12:57.000 --> 1:12:58.560
It's overwhelming.

1:13:06.840 --> 1:13:09.880
I know it seems hard right now.

1:13:09.880 --> 1:13:12.520
But this is a good thing.

1:13:12.520 --> 1:13:14.920
Wait till you see
how special these boys are.

1:13:16.880 --> 1:13:18.760
Such beautiful blue eyes.

1:13:23.360 --> 1:13:25.520
LUCY:

1:13:27.600 --> 1:13:30.120
I can't believe
this happened to me.

1:13:30.120 --> 1:13:32.680
‐ I know, I know.

1:13:32.680 --> 1:13:34.240
It's crazy.

1:13:46.000 --> 1:13:48.600
‐ What happened to your office?

1:13:48.600 --> 1:13:52.040
Wasn't it more culturally, uh...

1:13:52.040 --> 1:13:54.000
Weren't there, like...

1:13:54.000 --> 1:13:55.920
masks and‐‐

1:13:55.920 --> 1:13:59.160
Even your outfit
looks...different.

1:14:01.240 --> 1:14:03.640
‐ No.

1:14:03.640 --> 1:14:05.320
Nothing has changed.

1:14:06.840 --> 1:14:09.360
‐ Really?

1:14:09.360 --> 1:14:10.520
‐ Mm.

